---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Learn about MBA Blog, a professional writing brand focused on strategy, leadership, and useful business thinking.">
  <section class="page-header">
    <p class="eyebrow">About the brand</p>
    <h1>Professional thinking with a human pulse.</h1>
    <p>MBA Blog publishes practical essays for leaders, operators, builders, and students of business who want sharper judgment without the jargon fog.</p>
  </section>
  <section class="content-band two-column">
    <div>
      <h2>What this site is for</h2>
      <p>This is a place for clear frameworks, thoughtful analysis, and field-tested notes on how businesses make decisions, communicate priorities, and build momentum.</p>
      <p>The tone is professional but approachable: useful enough for a Monday morning meeting, readable enough for a quiet Sunday reset.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="callout">
      <h2>Core themes</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Strategy that changes decisions</li>
        <li>Leadership routines that reduce ambiguity</li>
        <li>Business writing that respects attention</li>
        <li>Operations that make good work repeatable</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
